This is a great recipe! As a professional chef, rarely in high volume, professional kitchens are potato salads made from scratch for service. Too many variables, WAY too much labor cost. This is a fantastic recipe to make for small catering events and luncheons. And according to the Iowa Dept of Inspections and Appeals, commercially produced mayonnaise is perfectly safe to be served at room temperature, providing it has not been served above 40 degrees for 4 hours or more.That is the rule for ALL foods. High volume kitchens get mayonnaise in 5 gallon buckets that are not even sealed. Key to this is the consistency of the recipe used in commercially produced mayonnaise. The hazards arise in the potatoes and the eggs, NOT the mayonnaise.

